<br>
I've grouped with many many Paladins in my time.  And the best ones don't have to be main tank to prove their worth.  They back up heal as needed.   They throw in some stuns here and there to keep casters from casting, particularly gate.  They do some crowd control if needed.  They help pull mobs off casters when a caster makes an oops.  They can root runners.  They can successfully tank unmezzable, unrootable adds.  They are effectively able to do a little of just about everything, and do it pretty darn well, if the player is skilled.  And for experience groups they do make a respectable main tank.<br>
<br>
If as a Paladin you feel you HAVE to be the main tank to have value, you're playing the wrong class.  You should be a Warrior.  Because a Warrior HAS to be the main tank to be fullfilling their full potential.  Otherwise they are merely mediocre damage dealers that should probably be replaced with a Monk or a Rogue.  Not so with a Paladin.  They can be either a Main or Secondary tank and still add significant value beyond their damage output.<br>
<br>
Warrior contributions?  Only two to speak of.  Damage absorbtion and damage dealing.  We have already agreed and accepted that our damage dealing is going to be third or fourth tier at best (Rogues, Rangers, Monks, Wizards, Mages with pets all do better damage).  Now you are saying we should also accept that our damage absorbtion (without disciplines) should only be slightly better than the other Plate melee and slightly worse than Monks?   And what exactly do we get to counter balance this?<br>
<br>
The Paladins are rending their clothes and beating their chest about how there just aren't that many places they can go to fight undead so they can solo effectively.  Well, those few places are WORLDS more than a Warrior has available.  Soloing is not a viable option through most of a Warrior's career.  Grouping is our only option.  And we don't think its unreasonble we a margin of attraction over an SK or a Paladin for that.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior>The Steel Warrior</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern>The Tavern</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.steelwarrior.org">The Steel Warrior website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

